items.name: Hailey Grice
items.description:
A request of @argus2968.

Hailey Grice is an American social media personality with more than 1M followers on Instagram.

This is a 240-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with a full batch size (i.e., batch size 6 and gradient acc. 3). Once again, I used @Scottymac's free online Colab, so thanks again, pal. :)

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my (usual) work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (hgr1ce-step-240:0.99), a woman as a movie star, hair upsweep updo, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"

items.name: The Executioner and Her Way of Life-characters-LoCon/FullCkpt Âá¶ÂàëÂ∞ëÂ•≥„ÅÆÁîü„Åç„ÇãÈÅì | Menou / TokitoAkari / Momo / Ashuna/ Pandemonium / ManonLibelle
items.description:
As usual, the model is trained with clip skip 1 on top of ACertainty and locon is extracted from the trained model

The locon should work on most models as I show in the xy plot

All the intermediate checkpoints can be found on https://huggingface.co/alea31415/shokei-shojo

It includes the following 7 characters from the series

  • Ashuna

  • Flare

  • ManonLibelle

  • Menou

  • Momo

  • Pandemonium

  • TokitoAkari

For Menou you have both

  • Menou

  • Menou child

For Pandemonium you have

  • Pandemonium (the classic one)

  • Maya Pandemonium (hair down version, the one after the end of the 5th tome of the novel)

  • Centipede Monster (monster version, the one at the 12th episode of the anime)

Maya Pandemonium is only trained on 6 images from the light novel: 2 colorful and 4 monochrome, but it should still be usable if you adjust things properly

The preview of Centipede Monster is only included for the FullCkpt version, because I guess it may make some uncomfortable (and anyway I do not think anyone would ever use it)

I split the styles into 3+1 during training

  • aniscreen (3928 images)

  • fanart (95 images)

  • colorful light novel / light novel (153 images)

As usual I use a lot of regularization images during training, in particular I also include most of my dataset for the in container loha (https://civitai.com/models/66021) here so I guess these concepts are more or less learned as well

The example images are either generated by the LoCon on top of VBP2.3

Or using a certain merge of the trained model

None of the images are generated in one shot

They generally include a lot of random draws, img2img, inpainting, and sometimes use of controlnet and regional prompter (for the case of multiple characters)

--

Just to complain, I really have a hard time figuring out what kind of images violate civitai TOS

I wanted to upload an image with Pandemonium on top of ManonLibelle who is lying in the blood (this one), but apparently this is detected as violation of TOS and gets removed automatically

In the mean time, we can easily find a lot of images that are on civitai that are more violent/horrible/bloody or whatsoever

Otherwise, although probably few people would ever be interested in a model for this

Shokei shojo is basically my favorite light novel, so I kind of feel that I must do it

Btw I saw an image of Menou from this discussion on outpainting of controlnet https://github.com/Mikubill/sd-webui-controlnet/discussions/1464 so I told myself it was time to get this model done

items.name: Desi Coffee
items.description:
A follow-up to my most popular textual inversion - Desigirl-NSFW. I created that, like I mentioned, because current checkpoints have a hard time calibrating for Indian looks and skin tone. While that textual inversion works fine, it is limited to generating just one skin tone, with the only way of varying the tone being to change weights, but that changes other parameters in the generation as well - including the 'looks' of the characters.

This LoRA, on the other hand gives you the flexibility to prompt for three skin tones through trigger words:

  • desilatte - this produces light skin-tones - but still something distinct from white or asian tones

  • desimocha - this produces medium skin-tones - what some might call 'olive' skin

  • desiespresso - this produces dark skin-tones, but still distinct from black or African skin tones

Since this is trained using a private collection of images of real people, there is an association of skin tone and facial features, but nothing too crazy for the most part.

Seems to work well with most photorealistic checkpoints, though I need to experiment some more.

Best settings, so far:

CFG: 5.5-7

Steps: ~20

Weight: 0.7-1.0

Sampler: euler a

As usual, comments and suggestions are welcome, as are questions. (Except ones on whether I can share the training data set, which I cannot - sorry.)

items.name: Stella Hoshii (VA-11 Hall-A) LoRA
items.description:
Stella Hoshii from VA-11 Hall-A: Cyberpunk Bartender Action, trained on animefull.

Around 0.8 weight works well. Her mechanical eye is tagged as 'eyepatch', prompt that when you want her to have it and prompt 'red eyes' when you don't want her to have it. When generating her default outfit, 'dress', 'short dress', 'elbow gloves', 'bare shoulders', and 'thighhighs' all help.

This LoRA was really hard to figure out how to train, but works surprisingly well! She did not have as much art as I expected she would, and her eye was a challenge to get to work right, but in the end it worked out. Some angles seem to make her eye generate a little funny, and sometimes the stripes on her dress can generate strangely, but that's about it!

This is an initial test release of my new mix, It is a combination of four popular models, info on pedigree at the bottom.

modelVersions.name: V2.0 - Mocha
modelVersions.description:
edit 06/24/23 I've taken down the model for 2.0, the more I use it the more I realize it's not up the the same level of quality as v1.0, once I've fixed those issues I'll re-release 2.0.

This updates quite a bit over the base model, first I retrained the original model by tweaking the percentages slightly, then I used that to generate around 250 high quality images with a variety of subjects, compositions, and overall vibe in a specific style which I then used to train a lora that I am affectionately referring to as "creamer" (more on that later), that was then merged into the model at 75% strength. After that I pruned the model with ema-only, fp16, and fix clip settings. The style has changed a bit from v1 of the model, but I think it gives consistently better results.

As for my Creamer LoRa, it produces similar results when used with my v1 model, I haven't released it but would be open to doing so if anyone is interested and prefers v1.
